canonical:
  title: 綠珠河次韻
  author: 崔淑精
  language: lzh
  text: 客中情况淡於秋驅馬悠悠過瑞州極目三韓飛鳥外春江不解洗離愁
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 綠珠河次韻
  author: 崔淑精
  language: lzh
  text: 客中情况淡於秋。驅馬悠悠過瑞州。極目三韓飛鳥外。春江不解洗離愁。
korean:
  title: 녹주하 차운
  author: 최숙정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    나그네의 정황이 가을보다 맑은데
    말을 몰아 유유히 서주를 지나간다
    끝까지 보이는 삼한땅 나는 새 밖이라
    봄 강물도 떠난 시름을 씻을 줄을 모른다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0750&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Responding to Green Pearl River
  author: Choe Suk-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A traveler's heart grows clearer than autumn itself,
    As I urge my horse through Rui Prefecture, drifting on.
    Beyond the birds that soar over the Three Han lands,
    Even spring's waters cannot wash away this sorrow of parting.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Three Han lands' refers to the Korean peninsula, a poetic allusion to the historical Three Kingdoms of Korea. This poem employs the technique of 'responding in rhyme' (차운), a literary tradition where poets compose new works using the rhyme scheme of an existing poem.
